Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain the @sweetcorn{1%pack} in a #sieve{}. Trim the @salad leaves{120%g} and roughly chop. Toss the salad leaves with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Slice the @brioche rolls{2} down through the middle (but not all the way through). Butter the bread with @?butter{to taste} if you like.

Pop onto a #baking tray{} and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}.

> You can toast your bread in the toaster if you like.

To a #bowl{}, add the @tuna chunks in water{1%tin}, @dried chilli flakes{1%sachet} and sweetcorn.

> Use less chilli flakes if you don't like spice.

Mix well with @aioli{1%sachet} and season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the salad leaves and tuna mix between the brioche rolls.

Scatter over the @crispy onions{1%sachet} then sandwich closed. Serve any remaining salad alongside.

To serve, slice each sandwich in half widthways. Divide between #plates{}.